        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T11:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.00/7–3145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser on Austrian Affairs,
                        Supreme Headquarters, Allied Expeditionary Force</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erhardt</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Verona</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31T18:00:00+02:00">July 31, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 31—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Re my 129, July 31, 3 p.m. Army authorities will deliver Pierre Laval to
                    French Commander at Innsbruck at 2000 hours tonight. Laval had intended to land
                    in Salzburg. Mrs. Laval is accompanying her husband. German pilot and co-pilot
                    former members of Luftwaffe, the only other occupants of plane are being
                    detained. <pb facs="0732" n="720" xml:id="pg_720"/> Among Laval’s possessions
                    was 10,000 American dollars in cash in 500 notes.</p>
                <p>Repeated Paris as 17.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Erhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[On October 9, 1945, Laval was sentenced to death for plotting against the
                        State and collaborating with the enemy. He was executed October 16,
                        1945.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
